## Server Daemon

The daemon must be running in `--dangerous` mode for agents to work (skips interactive permission prompts):

```bash
# Check status
ssh {{SERVER_HOST}} "{{SERVER_HOME}}/.local/bin/ty daemon status"

# If not running, start it (use full path for nohup):
ssh {{SERVER_HOST}} "nohup {{SERVER_HOME}}/.local/bin/ty daemon --dangerous > /tmp/ty-daemon.log 2>&1 &"

# Check logs
ssh {{SERVER_HOST}} "tail -20 /tmp/ty-daemon.log"

# Restart (stop then start)
ssh {{SERVER_HOST}} "{{SERVER_HOME}}/.local/bin/ty daemon stop"
```

**Common issues:**
- If tasks go to "blocked" immediately, the daemon likely isn't in `--dangerous` mode or isn't running
- Stale tmux sessions from old daemons can block new ones — use `ty sessions cleanup` and `tmux kill-server` before restarting
- Git identity is configured as `{{GIT_NAME}} <{{GIT_EMAIL}}>` — if this gets lost, the daemon can't create worktrees
- When sending input to a stuck agent prompt: `ty input <id> --key Down` and `ty input <id> --enter`

**Server project paths:** Each project is a git repo at `{{SERVER_HOME}}/projects/<project>/`. Task worktrees live at `{{SERVER_HOME}}/projects/<project>/.task-worktrees/<task-slug>/`. Git remotes use SSH aliases (e.g. `git@github-content:org/repo.git`).

## TaskYou Quick Reference

```bash
# Create a task
ty create "Task title" --project marketing --type draft --body "Detailed description"

# List tasks
ty list
ty list --project content

# Check board
ty board

# Execute a task (sends it to an agent)
ty execute <task-id>

# Retry a blocked/failed task
ty retry <task-id>

# Check task output
ty output <task-id>

# Send input to agent prompt
ty input <task-id> --key Down
ty input <task-id> --enter

# Check running agent sessions
ty sessions list

# Clean up orphaned sessions
ty sessions cleanup

# Close a task
ty close <task-id>

# Move task to different project
ty move <task-id> --project sales
```

